## Project Overview

PureModeDisabler is a small Android app (Java) that automatically disables "Pure Mode" and "App Check Risk" secure settings on HarmonyOS 4 devices. It monitors these settings via ContentObserver, re-disabling them whenever they change, and persists across reboots via a boot receiver.

## Build Commands

```bash
./gradlew assembleDebug       # Build debug APK
./gradlew assembleRelease     # Build release APK (with ProGuard/R8)
./gradlew installDebug        # Build and install on connected device
./gradlew clean               # Clean build artifacts
```

No test or lint infrastructure is configured.

## Setup

The app requires `WRITE_SECURE_SETTINGS` permission granted via ADB:
```bash
adb shell pm grant your.puremodedisabler android.permission.WRITE_SECURE_SETTINGS
```

## Architecture

Java classes in `app/src/main/java/your/puremodedisabler/`:

- **PureModeHelper** — Shared logic for disabling `pure_mode_state` (Secure, set to 1) and `app_check_risk` (Global, set to 0). Used by both SettingsMonitorService and PureModeWorker.
- **SettingsMonitorService** — Sticky service that registers a ContentObserver on the two settings for immediate response when alive. Debounces rapid-fire onChange callbacks (from both URIs or self-triggered writes) into a single check via `postDelayed` (500ms). Delegates to PureModeHelper.
- **PureModeWorker** — JobScheduler periodic job (every 15 minutes) that calls PureModeHelper. Acts as a fallback when HarmonyOS 4 kills the service after a few days. Uses `setPersisted(true)` to survive reboots.
- **BootReceiver** — Starts SettingsMonitorService and schedules PureModeWorker on boot (handles both BOOT_COMPLETED and QUICKBOOT_POWERON via manifest intent-filter).
- **MainActivity** — Single-screen UI with a log view (observes LogEventManager via callback listener) and a manual "Disable Pure Mode" button. Schedules PureModeWorker and starts the service on launch.
- **LogEventManager** — Singleton with a circular buffer (max 35 entries) exposed via a simple callback listener. Timestamps log entries and also writes to Android logcat with tag "PureModeDisabler".

Two layers of protection: SettingsMonitorService reacts instantly via ContentObserver while alive; PureModeWorker re-disables periodically via the system job scheduler even after the app process is killed.

## Dependencies

The app has zero library dependencies — it uses only Android framework APIs (JobScheduler, ContentObserver, Activity, etc.) to minimize APK size.

- **compileSdk/targetSdk:** 34 (Android 14)
- **minSdk:** 31 (Android 12)
- **Android Gradle Plugin:** 8.7.3
- **Package:** `your.puremodedisabler`

## Release Signing

Release signing is configured via Gradle project properties (`~/.gradle/gradle.properties`):

```properties
storeFile=~/.android/release.keystore
keystorePassword=yourpassword
keyAlias=release
keyPassword=yourpassword
```

If any property is missing, the release build produces an unsigned APK.
